  "story": "Every Saturday, three friends run neighbouring stalls at the riverside craft market, watched over by old Mr. Pemberton, who has kept the market ledger for forty years and still records every sale in sepia ink. This week each friend brought a different handmade craft and settled on a different price. Mr. Pemberton has misplaced the ledger page - match every friend to the craft they made and the price they charged.",
